DPN AS IT MOVS EWARDS. A SECOND LOW 988 WILL BE CENTRED IN THE NORWEGIAN
BASIN AND MOV SEWARDS THROUGH TUESDAY. MEANWHILE A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
1029 ACROSS SW APPROACHES WILL GRADUALLY DECLINE ON TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY.
A DEVELOPING AND COMPLEX ATLANTIC LOW IS LIKELY TO TRACK EWARDS ACROSS SCOTLAND
ON TUESDAY NIGHT BECMG CENTRED NEAR FORTIES 979 BY MIDDAY ON WEDNESDAY
BEFORE MOV ACROSS DENMARK TO BE CENTRED IN THE BALTIC 975 BY THURSDAY EVENING.
HOWEVER CONFIDENCE IS LOW FOR THE DETAILS OF THIS FEATURE. STRG OR NEAR
GALE WINDS MAY AFFECT NWERN PORTPATRICK INITIALLY BEFORE EASING MONDAY NIGHT.
